{"lemma": "أَحْسَن", "slug": "أَحْسَن", "root": "ح.س.ن", "root_slug": "ح-س-ن", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-س-ن", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "أَحْسَن", "root": "حسن", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 36}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 0}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n8003", "n8022"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%86"}}, "translations": {"en": "goodness", "fa": "نیکی", "ur": "نیکی", "tr": "iyilik", "id": "kebaikan", "bn": "ভালোবাসা", "es": "bondad", "fr": "bienfaisance", "de": "Güte", "ru": "благодеяние", "zh": "善行"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n8003", "headword_ar": "احسن", "root": "Hsn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "as an intrans. v.: see 1. ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He did that which was"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hasan", "text_ar": "حَسَن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good, comely,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pleasing; he acted well"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Msb;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he did a good deed:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Er-Rághib, TA:) [for]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHosaAnN", "text_ar": "اـِحْسَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_isaA='apN", "text_ar": "اـِسَا=ءَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) it differs from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_inoEaAmN", "text_ar": "اـِنْعَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in being to oneself and to another; whereas the latter is only to another: (TA:) and it surpasses"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EadolN", "text_ar": "عَدْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inasmuch as it means the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "giving more than one owes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "taking less than is owed to one;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "whereas the latter means the giving what one owes, and taking what is owed to one. (Er-Rághib, TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHosanotu A_ilayohi", "text_ar": "اَحْسَنْتُ اـِلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bihi", "text_ar": "بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I acted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "behaved, with goodness, well,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pleasing manner, towards him; did good to him; benefited him; conferred a benefit,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "benefits, upon him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: both signify the same: (S, TA:) and hence, in the Kur [xii. 101],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qado A^aHosana biY", "text_ar": "قَدْ اَحْسَنَ بِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_i*a A^axorajaniY mina Als~ijoni", "text_ar": "اـِذَ اَخْرَجَنِى مِنَ السِّجْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY~a", "text_ar": "اـِلَىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He hath acted well towards me, when he brought me forth from the prison"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (AHeyth, Az:) or, accord. to some, the verb in this case is made to import the meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laTafa", "text_ar": "لَطَفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is trans. by means of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He hath acted graciously with me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_iHosaAnu", "text_ar": "الاـِحْسَانُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also explained as meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_ixolaASu", "text_ar": "الاـِخْلَاصُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The being sincere,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "without hypocrisy;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the asserting oneself to be clear of believing in any beside God"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; which is a condition of the soundness, or validity, of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_iymaAn", "text_ar": "الاـِيمَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_isolaAm", "text_ar": "الاـِسْلَام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "together: and as denoting"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "watchfulness, and good obedience:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the continuing in the right way, and following the way which those [of the righteous] who have gone before have trodden;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this last being said to be the meaning in the Kur ix. 101. (TA.)       -A2-  As a trans. v.: see 2, in three places. ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AHsnhu", "text_ar": "احسنهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He knew it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA:) [or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he knew it well;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Er-Rághib, Msb;) and so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AHsn bihi", "text_ar": "احسن بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa yuHosinu biAlEarabiy~api", "text_ar": "هُوَ يُحْسِنُ بِالعَرَبِيَّةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He knows well the Arabic language."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA.) Hence the saying of 'Alee,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qiymapu Almaro'i maA yuHosinuhu", "text_ar": "قِيمَةُ المَرْءِ مَا يُحْسِنُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The value of the man is what he knows,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "knows well"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAsu A^abonaA='u maA yuHosinuwna", "text_ar": "النَّاسُ اَبْنَا=ءُ مَا يُحْسِنُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is another saying of 'Alee, meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Men are named,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "reputed, in relation to what they know, and to the good deeds that they do."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHosino bihi", "text_ar": "اَحْسِنْ بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^aHosanahu", "text_ar": "مَا اَحْسَنَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see 1, last sentence. You say also, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^uHayosinahu", "text_ar": "مَا اُحَيْسِنَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How very good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goodly,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is he!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; using the dim. form; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^umayoliHahu", "text_ar": "مَا اُمَيْلِحَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (S and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mlH", "text_ar": "ملح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)       -A3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a man, IAar)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sat upon a high hill,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heap, of sand, such as is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HasanN", "text_ar": "حَسَنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (IAar, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA", "S", "AHeyth", "Az"]}, {"entry_id": "n8022", "headword_ar": "اَحْسَنُ", "root": "Hsn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HasonaA='u", "text_ar": "حَسْنَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHaAsinu", "text_ar": "اَحَاسِنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HasanN", "text_ar": "حَسَنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHosanu", "text_ar": "الاَحْسَنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes the comparative and superlative degrees [of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HusonN", "text_ar": "حُسْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa AlA^aHosanu", "text_ar": "هُوَ الاَحْسَنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, is the better,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "best;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the more,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "most, goodly"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beautiful"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: (K:) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusonaY", "text_ar": "الحُسْنَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the fem.; as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^asomaA='u AlHusonaY", "text_ar": "الاَسْمَا=ءُ الحُسْنَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The best names;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "those of God; which are ninety and nine: (Jel in vii. 179:) it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~uwo'aY", "text_ar": "السُّوْءَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, K:) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHosanu", "text_ar": "الاَحْسَنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHaAsinu", "text_ar": "الاَحَاسِنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) In the saying, in the Kur [vi. 153 and xvii. 36],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa laA taqorabuwA maAla Alyatiymi", "text_ar": "وَ لَا تَقْرَبُوا مَالَ اليَتِيمِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_il~aA biAl~atiY hiYa A^aHosanu", "text_ar": "اـِلَّا بِالَّتِى هِىَ اَحْسَنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And approach ye not the property of the orphan,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to make use of it,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "except by that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "act"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is best"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be done with it, the meaning is, such an act as the taking care of it, and increasing it: (Bd:) or, as some say, the meaning is, the taking, of his property, what will [suffice to] conceal those parts of one's person that should not be exposed, and stay one's hunger. (TA.) [The fem.] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusonaY", "text_ar": "الحُسْنَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to accidents only: not to substances. (Er-Rághib, TA.) It means also, [as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That which is better,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that which is best."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And hence,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The good final"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ultimate state"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[appointed for the faithful]: (K:) so, it is said, in the Kur xli. 50. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The view,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vision, of God;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) accord. to some: but it is said that in the Kur x. 27, it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Paradise;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapN", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which there follows it, means the view, or vision, of the face of God. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Victory:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "martyrdom:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th, K:) whence, [in the Kur ix. 52,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusonayayoni", "text_ar": "الحُسْنَيَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one of the two best things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "victory or martyrdom."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh, Bd, Jel.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A_ilaAha A_il~aA A@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "لَا اـِلَاهَ اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Jel in xcii. 6 and 9.) The pl. of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusonaY", "text_ar": "الحُسْنَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusonayaAtu", "text_ar": "الحُسْنَيَاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHusanu", "text_ar": "الحُسَنُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, [the latter like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rujaEN", "text_ar": "رُجَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rujoEaY", "text_ar": "رُجْعَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but misunderstood by Freytag as syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmaHaAsinu", "text_ar": "المَحَاسِنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which next follows it in the K,]) neither of which is used without the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "S", "Bd", "Th"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}